                <note rend="inline" type="source">550.E1/263: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Child</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Genoa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-11T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 11—2:04 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>42. It was widely reported under a Washington date line in European newspapers
                    yesterday and today that at a meeting of the American Cabinet the statement was
                    made that the policy of the United States regarding the Government of Soviet
                    Russia coincides with that of the Allies. In so far as this statement is
                    susceptible of any interpretation, delegates in Genoa think that it means that
                    the United States has altered its attitude from that stated in the note of
                    Secretary Hughes declining to take part in the Conference.<note n="24"
                        xml:id="d678fn24">
                        <ref target="frus1922v01#pg_392">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p.
                            392</ref>.</note> You may desire to take some action in case the report
                    is unfounded. I have stated consistently that I have received no notice of any
                    change in our policy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Child</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
